       <h1>How the visualization community evaluates</h1>
            <p>
            Heidi Lam <i>et al.</i> surveyed 800 papers from four different visualization venues
            (InfoVis, EuroVis, VAST, and Journal of Information Visualization) between 1995 and 2011.
            They categorized 361 papers according to the kind of evaluation that was presented (approximately 400 papers did not evaluate their work).
            The chart below replicates Figure 1 in <a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1109/TVCG.2011.279">Heidi Lam <i>et al.'s paper</i></a> to show the occurrences of each evaluation category from 1995 to 2011. 
